5. ORION'S BUSINESS: GRELOD / HONORHALL
   NOT a dungeon. Social investigation + infiltration. No combat unless
   Orion makes it. Solution is Orion's -- don't suggest.
#####################################################################

--- 5.1 THE JOB + FOUR MASTERS ---
Orion holds a Brotherhood contract (client: Aventus Aretino) to kill Grelod the
Kind -- the most beloved woman in Riften, secretly running a child-abuse / Thieves
Guild training pipeline. He must also deal with Constance Michel.
NOTE -- THE RING CHECK-IN ALREADY HAPPENED (last session): Valerius ordered
  Constance enthralled THROUGH THE RING ("on my leash, not yours"). In doing so he
  accidentally taught Orion two things: (1) Orion CAN enthrall now (as long as he's
  fully sated), and (2) the Ring's surveillance has BLIND SPOTS -- Valerius isn't
  always listening. So the Constance choice below is fully armed and Orion knows
  he could hide a betrayal.
FOUR competing demands:
  - AVENTUS (client):  Grelod SUFFERS. Children KNOW they're free. Public.
  - MAVEN / GUILD:     Pipeline continues. Constance takes over. No disruption.
  - VALERIUS (Ring):   Constance enthralled through the Ring -> Court asset.
  - ORION himself:     Obey Valerius, or enthrall Constance for himself?
TIMELINE: a fortnight, no mechanical timer; Varon is the live nag. Pressure is
  narrative -- every day Grelod lives, the children suffer another day.

--- 5.2 BELOVED <-> ABUSE BEATS (the drumbeat: untouchable in public, monster in
    private). Interleave these. Every public beat says "no one will ever believe
    you"; every private beat says "she is exactly what Aventus said." ---

