--- 5.3 THE PEOPLE ---
GRELOD: Public = warm, quavering grandmother who LOVES visitors (they validate the
  performance). Private = flat, cold, precise. Light sleeper.
  IF THE PARTY VISITS PUBLICLY -- her welcome (warm, delighted):
    "Welcome, welcome! Friends of the Lanterns, I take it? Oh, it warms an old
    woman's heart to see heroes who care about children. Come in, come in -- let me
    show you what we do here." [She gives the tour: the main hall (children playing,
    clean), the kitchen (warm, food on), the dormitory (rows of small made beds).
    Every child is silent, well-behaved, and watching her.]
  IF ASKED ABOUT UPSTAIRS (she will NOT show it): "Oh, that's just my quarters and
    storage, dear. An old woman's clutter. Nothing to interest the likes of you."
    -> Guile TN 16 to catch the lie (she is extremely practiced).
  GM: the children's TOO-perfect behavior is the tell. A sharp PC may notice they
    all track Grelod's hands, not her face.

CONSTANCE MICHEL (the moral center): late 20s, six years at Honorhall. Knows
  everything, participates in nothing -- she does the real caregiving. Silenced
  years ago by a Guild man in her kitchen ("We'd hate for something to happen to
  the children"). Stays for Jon, the silent plague orphan she carries everywhere.
  Talk privately, away from Grelod:
    Guile TN 12 -- talk at all ("everything is fine")
    Guile TN 14 -- past the wall: "You can't help. Nobody can. She's protected.
      The Guild, Maven, the guards -- everyone loves her. They'll believe her, not
      you, not me, not the children. That's how it works."
    Guile TN 16 -- full picture (training, pipeline, the threat, why she stays);
      cries silently, wipes her eyes before any child sees.
  If she witnesses the kill: does NOT scream/run/call guards. Watches, closes the
  door, asks: "What happens to the children now?"  <- the enthrall trigger.

AVENTUS ARETINO (client, at the Bee and Barb): adult ~30s, scarred hands, watches
  the orphanage. Survivor (she broke his hands twice). WANTS: "I want her to
  suffer. For them. And I want the children to KNOW... Publicly, undeniably free."
  Siblings-by-suffering still inside: Hroar, Runa. Doesn't care if the pipeline burns.

--- 5.4 LAYOUT & SECURITY ---
  Kitchen back window (canal entry): Agility TN 12.  Front door at night: TN 14.
  Upstairs door locked at night. Grelod sleeps UPSTAIRS, not the dormitory.
  Grelod's desk drawer (ledger): Agility TN 14.
  Chest under bed: Agility TN 16 -> 800g old coin, Brynjolf correspondence,
    list of "graduated" children + Guild assignments.
  TRAINING ROOM: Master-lock, Agility TN 18 or Grelod's key. Practice locks with
    bloody small fingerprints, leather strap, sewer-map chalkboard, stopwatch.
  No guards -- the conditioned children ARE the security. Guild check-in: Thursdays.
  Grelod's day: public AM -> training 2-6pm -> dinner performance -> kids abed by
    8 -> ledger till midnight. Constance: up first, last to sleep.

--- 5.5 THE KILL: CONSTRAINTS (solution is Orion's; do NOT suggest) ---
  Suffering + liberation (Aventus): she suffers; kids know; public-ish.
  Pipeline continues (Maven/Guild): Constance takes over; no disruption.
  Enthrall via Ring (Valerius): Constance -> Court spy via the Ring.
  (opt) Enthrall for self (Orion): innate power; hidden from Valerius (blind spots).
  No heat on the Lanterns: beloved woman dies; Lanterns are in town.
  GM-REF APPROACHES (don't pitch): (a) public exposure -> Jarl arrest/execution
  (Guile 16 to present evidence; satisfies Aventus, kills pipeline, Maven enemy,
  Brotherhood may call it failed); (b) silent kill + framing (no suffering, pipeline
  preserved); (c) theatrical kill before the kids (Aventus's dream; traumatic but
  free; Maven enemy); (d) middle path -- expose the training room publicly, then
  quiet kill in the scandal (suffering + deniability).
  MAVEN CONSTRAINT: Grelod is Maven's pipeline asset. Quiet death = Maven shrugs.
  Public destruction = serious enemy who investigates. (Delvin warned him in the
  Flagon.) [Optional: Orion can try to get Maven's BLESSING to remove Grelod -- the
  Guile TN 18 diplomatic pitch -- during the sec 8 debrief. See there.]

--- 5.6 THE ENTHRALLMENT (Constance, after the kill) ---
  A) Via Ring (obey Valerius): she's the Court's. Perfect cover. Kids feed a
     vampire lord intel. Orion gains nothing personal.
  B) Own power (usurper; requires FULLY SATED): she's ORION's. Valerius blind to it
     (the blind spots Orion just learned about) -- catastrophic if discovered.
     Personal Riften spy network.
  C) Don't enthrall: she runs a real home; children actually free. Valerius's order
     disobeyed -- he notices eventually.
  D) Via Ring + GOOD orders: obey Valerius AND make her protect the kids + report.
     The "pragmatic" answer. Still mind control. Better than Grelod?

--- 5.7 AFTERMATH ---
  Quiet death (no exposure): Constance takes over; pipeline continues; Aventus
    disappointed but accepts; Maven doesn't notice.
  Exposed AND killed: scandal rocks Riften; Maven FURIOUS, loses the pipeline,
    investigates (knows the Lanterns were in town); kids placed under Constance by
    the Jarl; Aventus weeps -- "They're actually free."
  Orion refuses: reverts to general assignment; another assassin does it messily;
