--- 6.1 SECTION 1: THE KILLING FIELD (approach + guardian) ---
>>READ: "The path crests the ridge: Forelhost, the Last Redoubt -- a fortress of
  black stone fused into the mountain, walls angled like a clenched jaw. The
  twenty-foot iron gate stands OPEN -- not broken. Opened, as if someone walked
  out and never closed it. The ground between treeline and gate is wrong: shallow
  snow over BONES. Hundreds of ancient Nord skeletons in corroded armor, rotted
  siege ladders, rusted swords -- the Nordic army died OUTSIDE the walls, failing
  to breach. Among the dead, three figures pace: skeletal warriors in Dragon Cult
  robes, eye-sockets burning cold blue, patrolling the gate. They have done this
  for four thousand years."
INVESTIGATE:
  - The battlefield (Magic TN 12): no blade wounds -- the army was POISONED. The
    cult weaponized its own death. Forelhost was a bioweapons site from the start.
  - The open gate: oiled hinges, used within months -- Antoine's entry point.
  - The patrols (x3): fixed perimeter; attack anything entering; don't pursue past
    the treeline.
COMBAT -- THE ETERNAL WATCH:  DRAUGR SENTINEL x3 (TL1 Expert)
  HP 30 ea | DR 6 | IMMUNE poison/disease/cold | WEAK fire (DOUBLE)
  Might 17 / Agi 13 / Magic 15 / Guile 8
  Attacks: Ancient Nord Greatsword (melee, 10 dmg); Frost Breath (15ft cone, 8
    cold, Agi TN 15 half).
  PASSIVE Undying Loyalty: at 0 HP collapses 1 round, then rises with 10 HP next
    turn UNLESS burned or skull crushed (Might TN 14, or any fire to the downed body).
  WIN IT: fight (finish with fire/skull-crush) / fire spells stop reassembly / or
    sneak the patrol gap (Agi TN 14 vs Guile 8 -- easy).
  LOOT: 3x Ancient Nord Greatsword (100g ea); 1x Dragon Cult Amulet on the lead
    Sentinel (Magic TN 12 -- it's a KEY for sealed cult doors inside).
EXIT: gate open; corridor descends; air stale, metallic, faint sweet chemical smell.

--- 6.2 SECTION 2: THE OSSUARY (mass-suicide chamber; ward setup) ---
>>READ: "The corridor opens into a cathedral of death -- a hundred feet across,
  ceiling lost in shadow. Tiers of stone shelving hold BONES: thousands of
  skeletons, whole families curled together, preserved by cold dry air. Not
  scattered -- ARRANGED. Hands folded, heads facing center. They laid down and died
  willingly. At the center, a stone altar bears a massive tarnished iron cauldron,
  the air around it shimmering like heat-haze. Something radiates from the room:
  not warmth, not cold -- ABSENCE. The air feels thin, sound is muffled, magic
  harder to reach. On the far wall, a sealed stone door, recently modified -- fresh
  mortar, a bolted copper mechanism, and a copper plate in neat modern hand:
  'CONTAINMENT THRESHOLD. DO NOT BREACH WITHOUT PROTOCOL. THE WARD IS THE SEAL.'"
INVESTIGATE:
  - Arranged skeletons (Magic TN 12): poisoned, willingly; a religious mass suicide.
  - Cauldron/shimmer (Magic TN 14): nexus of the death ward. 4,000 yrs of
    concentrated death-energy = permanent anti-biological field; the most sterile
    place in Skyrim. Antoine built his lab inside it.
  - Sealed door: copper pressure-lock needs a sequence to open WITHOUT disrupting
    the ward. Warning in Antoine's hand.
  - Footprints: one person, boots; the most recent set goes ONE way -- OUT. He left
    and hasn't returned. Days old.
ALFONSO'S READ (no roll): "The ward is elegant. Thousands of deaths in one ritual
  moment made a permanent sterilization field. Your prodigy didn't build a
  laboratory -- he found one fanaticism already built. He just added a door."
  Alfonso learns: ward kills foreign biology; mechanism = safe access; FORCING it
  releases what's inside; use the mechanism as designed.

